title: 148.243 FEE AMOUNTS.
text:
The fee for licensure by examination is $105.
The reexamination fee is $60.
The fee for licensure by endorsement is $105.
The fee for registration renewal is $85.
The fee for reregistration is $105.
The fee for a replacement license is $20.
The fee for public health nurse certification is $30.
[Repealed, 2014 c 235 s 42; 2014 c 312 art 24 s 43]
The fee for verification of licensure status other than through Nursys verification is $20.
The fee for verification of examination scores is $20.
The fee for a copy of microfilmed licensure application materials is $20.
The fee for the initial application for nursing business registration is $100.
The fee for the annual application for nursing business registration is $25.
The fee for practicing without current registration is two times the amount of the current registration renewal fee for any part of the first calendar month, plus the current registration renewal fee for any part of any subsequent month up to 24 months.
[Repealed, 2017 c 57 s 6]
The service fee for a dishonored check is as provided in section 604.113.
The initial application fee for border state registration is $50. Any subsequent notice of employment change to remain or be reinstated on the registry is $50.
